# PrivateAppFlowy Commands

Self-hosted local `PrivateAppFlowy` only. Canonical paths: `~/.cursor/skills/privateappflowy/canonical-map.json`.

**Cursor IDE + CLI only** — Agent chat, `agent` / `cursor agent`, or `paf` on PATH. No standalone web publisher UI. **`/paf sync`** in chat means run `paf sync`.

## Verbs

| Verb | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `paf help` | Print cheat sheet |
| `paf drop "<title>"` | Session artifact → `private-docs/inbox/` |
| `paf new "<title>"` | Same as drop (title-only defaults to inbox) |
| `paf new <domain> "<title>"` | Explicit domain under `Docs/<Project>/…` |
| `paf publish` | Publish file(s) or `--source-root private-docs` |
| `paf sync` | Sync all `private-docs` |
| `paf find` | Search manifest |
| `paf open` | Open app / resolve page |
| `paf status` | Stack + auth + mapping |
| `paf guard` | Find docs outside `private-docs/` |
| `paf seed-templates` | Publish global templates to `Docs/Templates` |
| `paf baseline` | One-project migrate to canonical layout |
| `paf purge-legacy` | Remove old General/Wiki trees |

Domains: `engineering`, `gtm`, `inbox`, `series-a`, `series-b`.

```bash
python3 "$HOME/.cursor/skills/privateappflowy/scripts/publish_to_paf.py" <verb> --project-path "$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)"
```

## Rules

- Never publish into AppFlowy `General` or numbered wiki trees.
- Ambiguous session artifacts: `paf new inbox "<title>"` (classify later).
- After doc edits: agent runs `paf publish` or `paf sync` before finishing.
- `patpat` is not a PAF command.
